#: ../../users/explain/interactive.rst:14
msgid "When working with data, interactivity can be invaluable. The pan/zoom and mouse-location tools built into the Matplotlib GUI windows are often sufficient, but you can also use the event system to build customized data exploration tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users/explain/interactive.rst:18
msgid "Matplotlib ships with :ref:`backends <what-is-a-backend>` binding to several GUI toolkits (Qt, Tk, Wx, GTK, macOS, JavaScript) and third party packages provide bindings to `kivy <https://github.com/kivy-garden/garden.matplotlib>`__ and `Jupyter Lab <https://github.com/matplotlib/ipympl>`__.  For the figures to be responsive to mouse, keyboard, and paint events, the GUI event loop needs to be integrated with an interactive prompt. We recommend using IPython (see :ref:`below <ipython-pylab>`)."
